09/12/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva will meet with her US counterpart, Colin Powell, in Washington on Monday (9 December). She is expected to receive US support for the new government and will present her new regional initiative on collecting illegal weapons. She is expected to reiterate Macedonia's commitment to the fight against international terrorism, especially in view of last week's terror attack on the Macedonian consulate in Pakistan. (MIA - 08/12/02)
